### Vulnerability Classification Reference (for Audit Attribution & Evidence Evaluation)

| Vulnerability Type | Decisive Evidence Standard (sufficient to create ConfirmedVulnerability) |
|-------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| SQL Injection | Boolean/time difference reproducible, or response contains SQL syntax error |
| SSTI | Arithmetic probe echo (e.g., 49), or command execution output observable |
| Command Injection/RCE | Command output observable (direct echo, OOB response, reproducible delay) |
| LFI/Path Traversal | Sensitive file content successfully read |
| SSRF | Intranet request log, cloud metadata response, DNS resolution record |
| IDOR | Different identity accessing same resource with response difference proving privilege escalation |
| File Upload | Webshell accessible and command execution successful |
| XSS | Payload executes in target context (not merely reflected) |

**ConfirmedVulnerability promotion requirements**: At least two independent tests with consistent results, payload reproducible, confidence ≥ 0.9.
**PossibleVulnerability** is for single anomalous responses or initial suspicions not yet reproduced.
